WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
The useful signal in What actually improves modern l&d when teams are under pressure 03040500 is how decisions are run when pressure is high.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
As output scales, decision clarity becomes the real bottleneck. Last week in the quarterly capability review, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: volume around actually grows faster than attention and adoption.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So run one compact loop: brief, prototype, test with a small audience, then review evidence.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then scale only after one-week evidence shows real movement.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: teams drift when under expectations change faster than coaching adapts.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So where does modern fit when business transformation, not content volume, is the main game?

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
